{"id": "EUVD-2025-201870", "enisaUuid": "8951bdb0-75eb-3c66-b2d4-64be8d3575dc", "description": "In the Linux kernel, the following vulnerability has been resolved:\n\ndrm/amdkfd: Fix mmap write lock not release\n\nIf mmap write lock is taken while draining retry fault, mmap write lock\nis not released because svm_range_restore_pages calls mmap_read_unlock\nthen returns. This causes deadlock and system hangs later because mmap\nread or write lock cannot be taken.\n\nDowngrade mmap write lock to read lock if draining retry fault fix this\nbug.", "datePublished": "2025-12-09T04:09:49", "dateUpdated": "2025-12-20T08:52:05", "baseScore": 0.0, "references": ["https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/e2105ba1c262dcaa9573f11844b6e1e1ca762c3f", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/f7569ef1cf978aa87aa81b5e9bf40a77497f3685", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/7574f30337e19045f03126b4c51f525b84e5049e", "https://nvd.nist.gov/vuln/detail/CVE-2025-40332"], "aliases": ["CVE-2025-40332"], "assigner": "Linux", "epss": 0.02, "enisaIdProduct": [{"id": "0ca47c07-e8b8-3302-b1b4-50e7a878a218", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 6.17.8"}, {"id": "89baefa5-0c9c-32a4-8dbd-73e86b52cba1", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 6.12.58"}, {"id": "9fe0e185-4a15-3a89-955d-1b25606234fb", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "3.19"}, {"id": "a0ce4729-5e72-37d3-ba5f-1c5439735aa6", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 6.18"}, {"id": "b063a4ba-11d0-3343-b332-d42c269d2cb5", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "4a488a7ad71401169cecee75dc94bcce642e2c53 <7574f30337e19045f03126b4c51f525b84e5049e"}, {"id": "c9709497-023d-3991-9310-91b031c48783", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 0"}, {"id": "d34d8be2-6307-3e69-ba02-d1d770b7dff7", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "1da177e4c3f41524e886b7f1b8a0c1fc7321cac2 <f7569ef1cf978aa87aa81b5e9bf40a77497f3685"}, {"id": "e74a1db0-f8fc-3619-9142-3e17a4c2582b", "produ